Protecting Your Child’s Privacy Online
Coppa

✅ COPPA DISCLAIMER (READY TO USE)
Children’s Privacy (COPPA Notice)
This software is not directed to children under the age of 13.
The Telepathic Wind Robot — Cyber-Mystic Analyzer does not knowingly collect, store, transmit, or process personal information from children under 13, as defined by the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).
This program:
Does not require account creation
Does not request names, email addresses, or identifiers
Does not record, store, or transmit audio
Uses microphone input only for real-time, local visualization within the user’s browser
If you are under 13 years of age, do not use this software or activate the microphone.
If a parent or guardian believes that a child under 13 has used this software in a way that may involve personal information, please discontinue use immediately. No data is retained by this program.

“This software is intended for general audiences and experimental visualization use only.”

This software is intended for general audiences.
Children under the age of 13 may use this program.
No personal information is collected from any user, including children.
Audio input is processed only in real time within the browser and is
never recorded, stored, transmitted, or retained.

One Important Technical Warning ⚠️
If you ever add ANY of the following, you must revisit COPPA:
Saving audio
Saving frequency data tied to a session
User profiles
Analytics tied to IP/device
Cloud logging
“Share” features
Right now, you are safe because:
Everything dies in memory
Nothing leaves the page

COPPA works like this: Let’s say your child wants to use features on a site or download an app that collects their personal information. Before they can, you should get a plain language notice about what information the site will collect, how it will use it, and how you can provide your consent. ... https://consumer.ftc.gov/articles/protecting-your-childs-privacy-online   ...   How does COPPA work?  ...  What are my choices? ...  

